   Italian designer Gianfranco Ferre will replace Marc
Bohan as artistic director for the House of Dior.
   The burly, bearded architect-turned-fashion designer will show
his first collection for the French fashion house in July,
Christian Dior director Beatrice Bongibault said at a news
conference Thursday evening.
   Ferre will be responsible for designing haute couture clothes
and furs as well as luxury ready-to-wear clothes and furs for Dior.
Ferre will give up designing a haute couture collection under his
own name in Milan, Italy, but will retain his ready-to-wear label.
   Ms. Bongibault declined Thursday to provide details on why
Bohan, 62, a star in the French fashion world, had been abruptly
replaced.
