<FIRST>r w PM-US-PanamaGlance     05-12 0169</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-US-Panama Glance,150</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bush's Panama Declaration at a Glance</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a look at actions announced by
President Bush in response to the turmoil in Panama.
   The president Thursday:
   _Ordered an additional 2,000 U.S. troops into Panama, on top of
the 10,000 already there, ``to protect the lives of American
citizens.'' More than 20,000 U.S. civilians, many of them retirees,
live in the Central American country.
   _Denounced the regime of Panamanian military leader Gen. Manuel
Antonio Noriega and said he is recalling U.S. ambassador Arthur
Davis. Bush said the embassy staff also will be reduced.
   _Directed that U.S. government employees and their dependents
living outside of military bases be returned to the United States
or relocated to the bases along the Panama Canal.
   _Said the United States will support moves in the Organization
of American States and elsewhere to condemn Noriega.
   _Said the State Department will encourage representatives of
U.S. businesses operating in Panama to arrange for ``extended
absences'' of their dependents from the country.
</TEXT>
