<HEAD>Small Plane Crash Kills Four, Two Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MUNICH, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A private airplane crashed and
exploded in a ball of flame shortly after takeoff this morning,
killing four people, authorities said.
   Munich fire and rescue officials said the fifth person on board
the aircraft was injured. A man on the ground also suffered burns
when he tried to rescue the passengers, authorities said in a
statement.
   Officials said the single-engine Beechcraft plane, bound for
Budapest, Hungary, grazed the roof of a building near the airport
just outside the Bavarian capital and plunged into a garden.
   Police quoted witnesses as saying the plane failed to gain
altitude, lost power as its engine apparently stalled, went into a
spin and crashed shortly after takeoff.
