<HEAD>Popular Minister Found Guilty of Abusing Former Foster Child</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MARKHAM, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A community activist and clergyman from
Chicago's South Side has been convicted of sexually abusing a
teen-age foster son.
   The Cook County jury, which heard eight days of testimony,
deliberated more than seven hours before returning the verdict
Thursday night against the Rev. Paul Hall, a licensed foster parent
and founder of a boys club.
   He was found guilty of two counts of criminal sexual assault and
