<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Italy-Drugs     05-12 0086</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Italy-Drugs,0089</SECOND>
<HEAD>International Drug Trafficking Ring Broken Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police said Friday they broke up an international
drug trafficking ring and seized cocaine and heroin valued at more
than $7.2 million.
   Seventeen ring members were arrested Wednesday and Thursday,
including the alleged leader, Gustavo Mares Marrero, a Uruguayan.
   Police also seized 26 pounds of cocaine and 13 pounds of heroin.
   The heroin was bought in Bangkok, carried to Buenos Aires and
exchanged for cocaine to be sold in Rome, a police spokesman said.
</TEXT>
