<HEAD>Fire in Border Tunnel Kills Two, Injures 11</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOLZANO, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire swept through a tunnel on the
Italian-Austrian border, killing two Italian workers and injuring
11, police said Friday.
   Hundreds of cars and trucks lined up for about three miles on
either side of the Brenner highway tunnel as the busy road link
between Italy, Austria and West Germany was closed to traffic for
eight hours.
   The blaze spread quickly through the polyurethane cover of the
tunnel, causing thick, toxic smoke, police said.
   A team of 13 workers was on duty when the fire began in the
northbound lane of the tunnel, which has Italian customs at one end
and Austrian customs at the other.
   The injured, suffering from smoke inhalation, burns and
contusions, were taken to nearby hospitals where two were reported
in serious condition.
