<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Unilever     05-12 0209</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Unilever,0217</SECOND>
<HEAD>Unilever Posts 10 Percent Profit Gain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Unilever, the Anglo-Dutch household products
giant, said Friday its net profit rose 10 percent in the first
quarter, due to improvement in the company's operations outside
Europe.
   The company said its profit for the first three months of the
year came to 195 million pounds, which is about $326 million, or
10.44 pence a share, compared with 178 million pounds, or 9.53
pence a share, in the same period a year earlier.
   Sales rose 9 percent, to 4.33 billion pounds, about $7.2
billion, from 3.98 billion pounds a year earlier.
   Operating profit from Unilever's European businesses was little
changed at 205 million pounds, about $342 million, compared with
207 million pounds a year earlier, as mild weather cut into sales
of some food and drink products while promotional costs for some
detergent products increased.
   In North America, operating profit more than doubled to 66
million pounds, about $110 million, from 32 million pounds, helped
by first-time contributions from recent acquisitions of Durkee
Industrial Foods Corp. and Pennant Products Inc., a specialty
bakery products maker.
   Profit in the first quarter of 1988 was depressed by the
company's heavy investment to promote new detergent and dishwashing
brands, Unilever said.
</TEXT>
