<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fixed-rate home mortgages averaged 10.93
percent this week, according to a national survey released Friday
by the Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corp.
   That was down from 10.97 percent last week.
   On 1-year adjustable-rate mortgages, lenders were asking an
average initial rate of 9.36 percent this week, the same as the
week before.
